					<description><![CDATA[Ghibli Park, located in Nagakute, Aichi, Japan, opened its doors on November 1, 2022. The park is divided into five [&#8230;]]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-bc556a95 alignfull uagb-is-root-container"><div class="uagb-container-inner-blocks-wrap">
<div class="wp-block-cover"><span aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-cover__background has-background-dim"></span><img decoding="async" class="wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-1328" alt="Ghibli Park" src="/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/img12-e1711150289347.png" data-object-fit="cover"/><div class="wp-block-cover__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-cover-is-layout-constrained">
<div class="wp-block-uagb-advanced-heading uagb-block-d834e3aa"><h2 class="uagb-heading-text">Ghibli Park</h2></div>



<div class="wp-block-buttons is-layout-flex wp-block-buttons-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-button"><a class="wp-block-button__link wp-element-button" href="https://ghibli-park.jp/en/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Visit Website</a></div>
</div>
</div></div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-0cdff546 alignfull uagb-is-root-container"><div class="uagb-container-inner-blocks-wrap">
<p>Ghibli Park, located in Nagakute, Aichi, Japan, opened its doors on November 1, 2022. The park is divided into five distinct themed areas, each inspired by a different Ghibli film and nestled within the grounds of Expo 2005. These areas include Ghibli&#8217;s Grand Warehouse, The Hill of Youth, Dondoko Forest, Mononoke Village, and Valley of Witches.</p>



<p>While tickets for Ghibli Park may be pricier than those for the Ghibli Museum, it&#8217;s recommended for those seeking a fully immersive experience. With its expansive grounds and a diverse range of indoor and outdoor attractions, visitors can deeply immerse themselves in the enchanting worlds of various Ghibli films.</p>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-be08845e alignfull uagb-is-root-container"><div class="uagb-container-inner-blocks-wrap">
<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-3c17acf8">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" width="820" height="560" src="/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/img09.jpg" alt="No-face" class="wp-image-1322" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/img09.jpg 820w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/03/img09-300x205.jpg 300w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/03/img09-768x524.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 820px) 100vw, 820px" /></figure>



<p class="has-small-font-size">With 14 scenes in interactive exhibits, you can immerse yourself in your favourite Ghibli scenes.</p>
</div>



<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-65a3f208">
<div class="wp-block-uagb-advanced-heading uagb-block-19a12c0b"><h2 class="uagb-heading-text"><strong>Ghibli&#8217;s Grand Warehouse</strong></h2></div>



<p>The primary section of Ghibli Park  offers a diverse range of Ghibli-themed attractions. These include a screening room where exclusive short films are shown, multiple exhibition spaces, and a designated play area for children.</p>



<div class="wp-block-buttons is-content-justification-center is-layout-flex wp-container-core-buttons-is-layout-2 wp-block-buttons-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-button"><a class="wp-block-button__link has-ast-global-color-6-background-color has-background has-text-align-left wp-element-button" href="https://ghibli-park.jp/en/about/ghiblisgrandwarehouse.html" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">See Map</a></div>
</div>
</div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-6dbdcf07 alignfull uagb-is-root-container"><div class="uagb-container-inner-blocks-wrap">
<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-9a2a6e59">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full is-resized"><img decoding="async" width="820" height="560" src="/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/img03.jpg" alt="Baron's house" class="wp-image-1323" style="width:593px;height:auto" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/img03.jpg 820w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/03/img03-300x205.jpg 300w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/03/img03-768x524.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 820px) 100vw, 820px" /></figure>



<p class="has-small-font-size">&#8220;Cat Bureau&#8221; from &#8220;The Cat Returns,&#8221; recreated in a cat-sized building</p>
</div>



<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-08cc6da6">
<div class="wp-block-uagb-advanced-heading uagb-block-091c0538"><h2 class="uagb-heading-text">Hill of Youth</h2></div>



<p>The initial area visitors encounter upon entering the park from the Linimo station is the Hill of Youth. It highlights the iconic elevator tower from &#8220;Laputa: Castle in the Sky&#8221; and &#8220;Howl&#8217;s Moving Castle,&#8221; as well as a house from &#8220;Whisper of the Heart.&#8221; </p>



<div class="wp-block-buttons is-content-justification-center is-layout-flex wp-container-core-buttons-is-layout-3 wp-block-buttons-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-button"><a class="wp-block-button__link has-ast-global-color-6-background-color has-background has-text-align-left wp-element-button" href="https://ghibli-park.jp/en/about/hillofyouth.html" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">See Map</a></div>
</div>
</div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-7e30a4d5 alignfull uagb-is-root-container"><div class="uagb-container-inner-blocks-wrap">
<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-8f537285">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="820" height="560" src="/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/img01.jpg" alt="Satsuki and Mei's house" class="wp-image-1324" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/img01.jpg 820w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/03/img01-300x205.jpg 300w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/03/img01-768x524.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 820px) 100vw, 820px" /></figure>
</div>



<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-cf0c05ef">
<div class="wp-block-uagb-advanced-heading uagb-block-2e974a66"><h2 class="uagb-heading-text">Dondoko Forest</h2></div>



<p>Dondoko Forest, part of Ghibli Park, is highlighted by Satsuki and Mei&#8217;s house from &#8220;My Neighbor Totoro,&#8221; originally constructed for Expo 2005. The area underwent renovations in November 2021 and reopened alongside the rest of the park. Its name derives from the &#8220;Dondoko Odori&#8221; dance in the film. </p>



<div class="wp-block-buttons is-content-justification-center is-layout-flex wp-container-core-buttons-is-layout-4 wp-block-buttons-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-button"><a class="wp-block-button__link has-ast-global-color-6-background-color has-background has-text-align-left wp-element-button" href="https://ghibli-park.jp/en/about/dondokoforest.html" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">See Map</a></div>
</div>
</div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-b1a236fc alignfull uagb-is-root-container"><div class="uagb-container-inner-blocks-wrap">
<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-8c92b08c">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="820" height="546" src="/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/mononoke_forest.jpeg" alt="Irontown" class="wp-image-1325" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/mononoke_forest.jpeg 820w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/03/mononoke_forest-300x200.jpeg 300w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/03/mononoke_forest-768x511.jpeg 768w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/03/mononoke_forest-272x182.jpeg 272w" sizes="(max-width: 820px) 100vw, 820px" /></figure>
</div>



<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-448874a9">
<div class="wp-block-uagb-advanced-heading uagb-block-3312865c"><h2 class="uagb-heading-text">Mononoke Village</h2></div>



<p>Mononoke Village is dedicated to Princess Mononoke, reflecting settings like Irontown and Emishi Village from the film. The area displays models of the mystical creatures seen in the movie and feature a village settlement, a traditional charcoal burner&#8217;s hut, and an interactive area for visitors to engage with iron forge bellows.</p>



<div class="wp-block-buttons is-content-justification-center is-layout-flex wp-container-core-buttons-is-layout-5 wp-block-buttons-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-button"><a class="wp-block-button__link has-ast-global-color-6-background-color has-background has-text-align-left wp-element-button" href="https://ghibli-park.jp/en/about/mononoke.html" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">See Map</a></div>
</div>
</div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-729b59c6 alignfull uagb-is-root-container"><div class="uagb-container-inner-blocks-wrap">
<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-8d2734e4">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="820" height="547" src="/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/img01-2.jpg" alt="Howl's castle" class="wp-image-1326" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/img01-2.jpg 820w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/03/img01-2-300x200.jpg 300w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/03/img01-2-768x512.jpg 768w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/03/img01-2-272x182.jpg 272w" sizes="(max-width: 820px) 100vw, 820px" /></figure>
</div>



<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-6cb55df2">
<div class="wp-block-uagb-advanced-heading uagb-block-f3b3ff3b"><h2 class="uagb-heading-text">Valley of Witches</h2></div>



<p>The newly opened Valley of Witches, inspired by &#8220;Kiki&#8217;s Delivery Service&#8221; and &#8220;Howl&#8217;s Moving Castle,&#8221; features restaurants, small amusements, and replicas of Kiki&#8217;s home and Gütiokipänjä bakery. It includes a towering, life-size Howl&#8217;s Moving Castle with the iconic hat shop. Set to be the park&#8217;s largest area.</p>



<div class="wp-block-buttons is-content-justification-center is-layout-flex wp-container-core-buttons-is-layout-6 wp-block-buttons-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-button"><a class="wp-block-button__link has-ast-global-color-6-background-color has-background has-text-align-left wp-element-button" href="https://ghibli-park.jp/en/about/valleyofwitches.html" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">See Map</a></div>
</div>
</div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-957924fc alignfull uagb-is-root-container"><div class="uagb-container-inner-blocks-wrap">
<p>As well as Ghibli Museum, visitors must make advanced reservations for their specific entry date. Tickets cannot be bought at the park.</p>



<div class="wp-block-buttons is-content-justification-right is-layout-flex wp-container-core-buttons-is-layout-7 wp-block-buttons-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-button"><a class="wp-block-button__link wp-element-button" href="https://ghibli-park.jp/en/ticket/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Get Tickets</a></div>
</div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-a7146a93 alignfull uagb-is-root-container"><div class="uagb-container-inner-blocks-wrap">
<p class="has-medium-font-size">Trailer</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-twitter wp-block-embed-twitter"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<div class="ast-oembed-container " style="height: 100%;"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="ja" dir="ltr">ジブリパークチケット販売告知映像です。<br>制作はスタジオジブリ。音楽は久石譲さん。ナレーションは鈴木さんです。 <a href="https://t.co/1LDYCjKiRX">pic.twitter.com/1LDYCjKiRX</a></p>&mdash; ジブリパーク GHIBLI PARK (@ghibliparkjp) <a href="https://twitter.com/ghibliparkjp/status/1554039911874850816?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">August 1, 2022</a></blockquote><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></div>
</div></figure>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-db2266bf alignfull uagb-is-root-container"><div class="uagb-container-inner-blocks-wrap">
