					<description><![CDATA[The Ghibli Museum is located in Inokashira Park in Tokyo. This museum features a theater screening scenes from films, a [&#8230;]]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-809bd9e9 alignfull uagb-is-root-container"><div class="uagb-container-inner-blocks-wrap">
<div class="wp-block-cover"><span aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-cover__background has-background-dim"></span><img decoding="async" class="wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-1307" alt="Ghibli museum" src="/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/photo0jpg.jpg" data-object-fit="cover"/><div class="wp-block-cover__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-cover-is-layout-constrained">
<div class="wp-block-uagb-advanced-heading uagb-block-7a93958d"><h2 class="uagb-heading-text">Ghibli Museum</h2></div>



<div class="wp-block-buttons is-layout-flex wp-block-buttons-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-button"><a class="wp-block-button__link wp-element-button" href="https://www.ghibli-museum.jp/en/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Visit Website</a></div>
</div>
</div></div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-45645b86 alignfull uagb-is-root-container"><div class="uagb-container-inner-blocks-wrap">
<p>The Ghibli Museum is located in Inokashira Park in Tokyo.  This museum features a theater screening scenes from films, a playful area for children, a rooftop garden, and exhibits related to their movies, including Spirited Away. <br>It is a major attraction, drawing in countless visitors, and tickets are in extremely high demand, making them limited in availability.</p>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-a13ddcfc alignfull uagb-is-root-container"><div class="uagb-container-inner-blocks-wrap">
<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-6495c542">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="554" src="/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/totoro031-1024x554.jpg" alt="Catbus" class="wp-image-1306" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/totoro031-1024x554.jpg 1024w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/03/totoro031-300x162.jpg 300w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/03/totoro031-768x415.jpg 768w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/03/totoro031-1536x830.jpg 1536w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/03/totoro031.jpg 1920w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>
</div>



<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-d7d76979">
<p>On the second floor, visitors can interact with one of the beloved characters from Studio Ghibli films: a large stuffed Catbus from &#8220;My Neighbor Totoro!&#8221; It&#8217;s a dream come true for many to have the chance to touch the Cat Bus.<br>*Only children aged 12 and under are allowed to enter and play inside.</p>
</div>



<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-a53488cf">
<p>Atop the museum, you&#8217;ll find a garden featuring a life-size, five-meter-tall statue of a robot from Castle in the Sky.</p>
</div>



<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-e34d4333">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="683" src="/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/ghibli-museum-1024x683.jpg" alt="Laputan robot" class="wp-image-1308" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/ghibli-museum-1024x683.jpg 1024w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/03/ghibli-museum-300x200.jpg 300w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/03/ghibli-museum-768x512.jpg 768w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/03/ghibli-museum-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/03/ghibli-museum-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, /wp-content/uploads/2024/03/ghibli-museum-272x182.jpg 272w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>
</div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-72ba93cc alignfull uagb-is-root-container"><div class="uagb-container-inner-blocks-wrap">
<p>Planning to visit the Ghibli Museum? Remember, tickets sell out fast, so plan ahead. They sell out tickets in advance and no ticket is available to purchase at museum! You&#8217;ll need to check the museum&#8217;s official website for their opening calendar before deciding on your visit date.</p>



<div class="wp-block-buttons is-layout-flex wp-block-buttons-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-button"><a class="wp-block-button__link wp-element-button" href="https://www.ghibli-museum.jp/en/tickets/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Get Tickets</a></div>
</div>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-72659f5f alignfull uagb-is-root-container"><div class="uagb-container-inner-blocks-wrap">
<p class="has-small-font-size">Reference<br>Ghibli Museum Mitaka &#8211; all you need to know before you go (2024). Tripadvisor. (n.d.). https://www.tripadvisor.ca/Attraction_Review-g1060901-d581684-Reviews-Ghibli_Museum_Mitaka-Mitaka_Tokyo_Prefecture_Kanto.html</p>
</div></div>
]]></content:encoded>
					
